1. To create a child-view binder, you will need to require the child view into your parent view's config, and add it into the rivetsConfig childViewBinders hash.

```javascript
rivetsConfig : {
    formatters       : [formatters],
    childViewBinders : {
        'project-view' : ProjectView
    }
}
```

1. This will create a binding available in the template (in the example it would be 'data-rv-new-project-view')

2. You can bind to a collection, or model, or hash and have them available in the child view as 'this.collection' (for collection), 'this.model' (if you have bound a model or hash).
